The most likely cause is that you haven't set the page's `BindingContext` to your ViewModel. Bindings won't resolve without it.

**Fix â€” set BindingContext in code-behind:**

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

**Also ensure** your ViewModel implements `INotifyPropertyChanged` (or uses `[ObservableProperty]` from the MVVM Community Toolkit) so the UI updates when values change:

```csharp
public partial class MyViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string title;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string description;
}
```

**TL;DR:** No `BindingContext` â†’ bindings have nothing to resolve against â†’ blank labels.
